##After staying in Wuhan, I took my 3 day old son to live in my car

Ruan Xiangyin, a citizen of Huanggang City, Hubei Province, went to Han province to give birth with his "panda blood" wife. After the baby was born, they were stuck on a pass and there were no hotels in Wuhan to receive them. Ruan Xiangyin can only take his mother-in-law, wife and newborn son living in the car.

On the evening of February 24,2020, under the coordination of the Wuhan Hongshan District Epidemic Prevention Headquarters, Ruan Xiangyin checked into a hotel in the district and ended her days on the bus.

Here is Nguyen Tuong Eun's dictation:

I am Huanggang Hongan County, 31 years old, engaged in the automobile industry, the eldest daughter is 2 years old, and last year his wife was pregnant. But we're both happy and sad.

My wife is "Panda Blood" (RH blood type) , fertility is always a very troublesome thing. When I was in labor, I didn't expect to encounter such a big thing as new coronary pneumonia.

When we went to the Hongan County Hospital and the Huanggang Hospital for the check-up, the doctors told us that the whole area was short of the blood for fear of accidents. They suggested that we come to Wuhan instead. I had to take my wife out of town.

Before going out of town, we first opened a pass to the local government, which is actually a letter of introduction, explaining our current situation and the reason why we had to go to Wuhan for medical treatment.

On February 4th, 2020, we headed to Tongji Hospital to prepare for Labor because our eldest daughter was born in Tongji. But seeing that the Tongji hospital basically only accepts the new coronary pneumonia patient's condition, we decided to go to Hubei Province maternal and child health care hospital to carry on the Prenatal check-up. The prenatal examination went well that day. With the pass from Hong'an County, we also got out of Wuhan and went home.

On February 12,2020, as the due date approached, my mother in law and I took my wife to Wuhan. My wife stayed in the delivery room for a few days while my mother-in-law and I made do in the car.

At 10 a.m. on the 20th, a son was born. In fact, the provincial maternal and child health hospital did not "panda blood" reserves, but fortunately, mother and Son Safe, everything is very smooth. For a few days, my mother-in-law and I were able to take care of my wife in a third-floor hospital room, but at least we had a place to stay.

The baby is just 3 days old

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 9 am on the 23rd, after all the wife's tests came out, the ward doctor told us to leave the hospital. The beds in the provincial maternity and Child Care Hospital are also very tight, and we understand very well. At noon, the four of us decided to drive home.

And to my surprise, we were never getting out.

At 1 pm that day, we drove to the Qinglong Toll Station and were stopped by the epidemic prevention and control personnel. I also showed them the letter of introduction, but was told only to use the "wuhan-issued pass. ". Even if the wife holds the newborn baby to show them, still communication is ineffective, we can only stop.

At 3:00 this morning, we decided to try again, and we got stopped. We had no choice but to go back to the hospital parking lot, where three adults and a newborn baby slept in the car for two hours. My car is a Volkswagen, the car space is very small, the air is not good, the child kept crying, we three adults are too anxious to do nothing but cry with him, there is nothing to do.

At the bottom of the tank, the family had to find a nearby gas station to fill up. Photo courtesy of the respondents.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Seeing this, we decided to settle down in Wuhan first. But we are not familiar with Wuhan, near the hospital to find more than a dozen hotels, either closed, or the hotel was requisitioned. We also went to the local police station, the police have a very good attitude, especially warm-hearted, driving us to a special placement of stranded foreigners hotel. But in this case, who can say for how long? As soon as the hotel heard that my son had just been born, they did not dare to accept him, for fear that the child would be too young, for a long time, and no one would be able to bear the responsibility for any problems.

This afternoon, we went to the Wuchang District government and heard that the Wuchang District Prevention and control headquarters was working inside. I met a man at the door who also wanted to apply for a pass. He said he was from Chongqing and had hiked for more than an hour to get here. But the security guard, after talking to the staff inside by telephone, told us that we could not get a pass at the moment.

Later, we communicated with the staff by telephone. I was told that I could apply for a pass after submitting the receipt certificate of my place of residence, the health certificate of the hospital and the application for leaving China. But then she found out that the provincial mch hospital was in Hongshan District and couldn't get us a pass. We can only try our luck with the Hongshan district government again,

On the evening of February 24, under the coordination of the Hongshan District Defense and Control Command, the police of the Lo 'Nan police station found us a hotel that was acceptable in the area under their jurisdiction. Police are very warm-hearted, told us to try not to go out, and told us that the community can give us shopping.

Now we don't have to live in a car. But frankly, the kids are still young, and we'd like to get back home as soon as possible. Home after home, home or fixed-point quarantine, how good.
